text: Kandrykul () is a rural locality (a selo) in Nikolayevsky Selsoviet, Tuymazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 547 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 33 km from Tuymazy, 7 km from Nikolayevka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Tuymazinsky District
title: Kandrykul
